Professional?

00:01:14.061 --> 00:01:14.560
Wow.

00:01:14.560 --> 00:01:15.270
That's great.

00:01:15.270 --> 00:01:16.940
Looks like more
than half the room.

00:01:16.940 --> 00:01:18.540
And I take it most
of the rest of you

00:01:18.540 --> 00:01:20.250
are probably game players?

00:01:20.250 --> 00:01:20.797
OK.

00:01:20.797 --> 00:01:22.130
Well, you're in the right place.

00:01:22.130 --> 00:01:24.240
Let's get going.

00:01:24.240 --> 00:01:27.360
I've been a professional
game developer since 1980.

00:01:27.360 --> 00:01:30.090
And in all that time,
I've only seen really

00:01:30.090 --> 00:01:32.010
one constant in this industry.

00:01:32.010 --> 00:01:35.260
And that's been the change that
it goes through so quickly.

00:01:35.260 --> 00:01:38.000
So we've grown from this
tiny little hobbyist

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:41.960
market where we were putting
floppy disks in Ziploc bags

00:01:41.960 --> 00:01:44.830
with printed out
pages of instructions

00:01:44.830 --> 00:01:48.710
to this huge industry where it
touches on almost everybody who

00:01:48.710 --> 00:01:50.570
uses information technology.

00:01:50.570 --> 00:01:53.600
It's just been amazing to
see the growth over time.

00:01:53.600 --> 00:01:57.560
And really, there's no
sign of it slowing down.

00:01:57.560 --> 00:02:00.650
I've never, in fact, seen as
much promise in the industry

00:02:00.650 --> 00:02:01.720
is there is right now.

00:02:01.720 --> 00:02:03.250
If you just think
about everything

00:02:03.250 --> 00:02:07.410
that's going on with consoles,
mobile, web, new growth areas

00:02:07.410 --> 00:02:10.979
like wearables and VR,
everything is thriving.

00:02:10.979 --> 00:02:15.170
And we're supporting all
those things here at Google.

00:02:15.170 --> 00:02:17.010
But any support
system for something

00:02:17.010 --> 00:02:20.980
as complex and multifaceted as
the games industry has become

00:02:20.980 --> 00:02:22.480
can be a little bit
hard to picture.

00:02:22.480 --> 00:02:23.938
You've got a lot
of things plugging

00:02:23.938 --> 00:02:27.230
into other things and things
that depend on other things.

00:02:27.230 --> 00:02:29.330
So describing what
we do here at Google

00:02:29.330 --> 00:02:31.710
is similarly complex at times.

00:02:31.710 --> 00:02:35.160
We've got hardware, operating
systems, software packages,

00:02:35.160 --> 00:02:36.740
and services to
describe that all

00:02:36.740 --> 00:02:38.510
interconnect in all these ways.

00:02:38.510 --> 00:02:41.070
But the nice thing is that
we in the games industry

00:02:41.070 --> 00:02:43.480
have a long history
of having to describe

00:02:43.480 --> 00:02:45.170
these kind of complex things.

00:02:45.170 --> 00:02:49.220
You think about build trees
or technology trees, skills

00:02:49.220 --> 00:02:51.050
or magic abilities
that are associated

00:02:51.050 --> 00:02:53.830
with different character
classes, it's the kind of thing

00:02:53.830 --> 00:02:55.360
that we do all
the time in games.

00:02:55.360 --> 00:02:57.870
So if you'll excuse me
for going a bit meta,

00:02:57.870 --> 00:03:02.020
let me talk about applying
that analogy here to Google.

00:03:02.020 --> 00:03:04.570
I think it's really,
generally, pretty appropriate

00:03:04.570 --> 00:03:09.030
because, as game developers,
we're all really on quests

00:03:09.030 --> 00:03:10.252
in the work that we do.

00:03:10.252 --> 00:03:12.210
We're trying to build
the game, and in the way,

00:03:12.210 --> 00:03:15.290
we have battles with bugs--
sometimes giant bugs--

00:03:15.290 --> 00:03:17.240
and deadline dragons.

00:03:17.240 --> 00:03:20.450
We're all after that fabled
golden chest of loot at the end

00:03:20.450 --> 00:03:22.965
and want to survive to be
able to launch our next quest

00:03:22.965 --> 00:03:24.530
and keep going.

00:03:24.530 --> 00:03:28.560
So think of Google as supplying
the equipment, the armor

00:03:28.560 --> 00:03:30.580
to level up your skills.

00:03:30.580 --> 00:03:32.840
And whether you're just a
level seven coder, looking

00:03:32.840 --> 00:03:35.290
for a new API to arm
yourself, or maybe

00:03:35.290 --> 00:03:37.570
you're a level 20 game
producer and you're

00:03:37.570 --> 00:03:40.210
trying to map your
path to the fabled land

00:03:40.210 --> 00:03:41.620
of mobile engagement.

00:03:41.620 --> 00:03:44.060
Maybe you're a
demi-CEO and you're

00:03:44.060 --> 00:03:46.120
in search of a
monetization spell.

00:03:46.120 --> 00:03:48.250
We can help you here.

00:03:48.250 --> 00:03:51.410
So this is a rather
schematic skill tree.

00:03:51.410 --> 00:03:54.540
Unlike games, where one thing
directly depends on another,

00:03:54.540 --> 00:03:56.840
it's a bit more
complex here at Google.

00:03:56.840 --> 00:03:58.730
So I'm keeping it simple.

00:03:58.730 --> 00:04:01.710
But if you picture the operating
systems and the hardware

00:04:01.710 --> 00:04:05.200
platforms that run your games
as your choice of a character

00:04:05.200 --> 00:04:07.960
faction or a hero a class,
and the services that we

00:04:07.960 --> 00:04:11.350
offer as skills, or
spells, or power ups,

00:04:11.350 --> 00:04:13.850
you'll find it easier to
see which ones of those

00:04:13.850 --> 00:04:16.870
apply to you, and your games,
and your game development,

00:04:16.870 --> 00:04:19.320
and be able to mix and
match as you go along.

00:04:19.320 --> 00:04:21.279
So let me go through
some of these.

00:04:21.279 --> 00:04:23.160
For each of these
services as power ups,

00:04:23.160 --> 00:04:24.600
I'm going to be
showing cards here

00:04:24.600 --> 00:04:27.250
that will talk about
aspects of game development

00:04:27.250 --> 00:04:29.200
they help, whether it's
building your game,

00:04:29.200 --> 00:04:31.940
growing your audience,
engaging that audience,

00:04:31.940 --> 00:04:34.490
or monetizing the game.

00:04:34.490 --> 00:04:37.140
So let's start with
the operating systems.

00:04:37.140 --> 00:04:38.810
The Android OS.

00:04:38.810 --> 00:04:42.380
We give you the API libraries
and the software tools

00:04:42.380 --> 00:04:45.220
necessary to build, test,
and debug your game.

00:04:45.220 --> 00:04:47.780
And Android's reach
is just enormous.

00:04:47.780 --> 00:04:51.666
Every day, over a million new
Android devices are activated.

00:04:51.666 --> 00:04:53.540
With Chrome, you can
build cutting edge games

00:04:53.540 --> 00:04:58.370
for the web that use tools
to make it scalable and easy

00:04:58.370 --> 00:05:01.260
to deploy, able to run
on multiple platforms.

00:05:01.260 --> 00:05:03.760
And the Chrome Web Store
helps the interested users

00:05:03.760 --> 00:05:05.630
to find your games.

00:05:05.630 --> 00:05:09.320
And then we have all the devices
that these games can run on.

00:05:09.320 --> 00:05:12.310
Android phones and tablets are
the largest potential platform

00:05:12.310 --> 00:05:15.510
for games worldwide, with
over a billion installations.

00:05:15.510 --> 00:05:17.780
Just think about a
billion installations out

00:05:17.780 --> 00:05:20.270
there will be seeing games
with a billion players

00:05:20.270 --> 00:05:22.470
at some point in the future.

00:05:22.470 --> 00:05:24.430
Last year, we
announced Android Wear.

00:05:24.430 --> 00:05:27.410
You can include
wearables, like watches,

00:05:27.410 --> 00:05:29.630
as part of your game's
notification system.

00:05:29.630 --> 00:05:32.100
Or as we saw with some
of the great new things

00:05:32.100 --> 00:05:35.010
going on at the keynote,
watches themselves are really

00:05:35.010 --> 00:05:36.500
an interesting,
standalone device

00:05:36.500 --> 00:05:37.820
to consider running games on.

00:05:37.820 --> 00:05:40.150
There's just so much you
can do with them now.

00:05:40.150 --> 00:05:44.110
And also to go to a bigger
screen, we have Android TV.

00:05:44.110 --> 00:05:46.620
You can engage players with a
variety of hardware solutions

00:05:46.620 --> 00:05:47.120
there.

00:05:47.120 --> 00:05:49.610
It's out on a lot of
televisions that are coming out

00:05:49.610 --> 00:05:52.010
in the very near future.

00:05:52.010 --> 00:05:54.830
And now, we also are adding
games built for Chromecast

00:05:54.830 --> 00:05:57.500
to join Android's
living room story.

