And they have a ton
of sensors to capture

00:11:39.220 --> 00:11:42.830
your touch and gestures to
enhance your gaming experience.

00:11:42.830 --> 00:11:44.480
With all this technology
that you have,

00:11:44.480 --> 00:11:46.063
wouldn't it be great
if you could just

00:11:46.063 --> 00:11:48.860
experience the fun of playing
a game in the same room

00:11:48.860 --> 00:11:50.300
as your friends?

00:11:50.300 --> 00:11:53.230
With Google Cast games, you
can recapture that magic

00:11:53.230 --> 00:11:55.284
of sitting down in
your house and playing

00:11:55.284 --> 00:11:56.950
a game in the same
room as your friends,

00:11:56.950 --> 00:11:59.200
all on your own devices
connected to a really

00:11:59.200 --> 00:12:01.930
big screen with great audio.

00:12:01.930 --> 00:12:03.980
My name is Nathan
Camarillo, a Product Manager

00:12:03.980 --> 00:12:05.752
on the Google Cast team.

00:12:05.752 --> 00:12:08.210
And today, I want to tell you
more about these technologies

00:12:08.210 --> 00:12:09.870
and some of the great
improvements our team has

00:12:09.870 --> 00:12:12.620
made recently to enable new
experiences in the living room.

00:12:15.290 --> 00:12:17.930
Goog Cast is designed to
use your mobile device

00:12:17.930 --> 00:12:20.880
to drive experiences on
home entertainment devices.

00:12:20.880 --> 00:12:25.240
For example, we see a 45%
increase in YouTube watch time

00:12:25.240 --> 00:12:28.390
upon a Chromecast activation.

00:12:28.390 --> 00:12:30.620
And Chromecast is
really easy to use.

00:12:30.620 --> 00:12:33.310
You just pick the content
using the apps you already

00:12:33.310 --> 00:12:36.030
know and love, you
tap the Cast button,

00:12:36.030 --> 00:12:37.675
and you enjoy the
content on your TV.

00:12:37.675 --> 00:12:40.220
It's pretty easy.

00:12:40.220 --> 00:12:42.500
Our first product
was the Chromecast,

00:12:42.500 --> 00:12:44.600
which has sold over
17 million units,

00:12:44.600 --> 00:12:46.970
and was the top selling
streaming device, including

00:12:46.970 --> 00:12:50.610
streaming boxes, in 2014.

00:12:50.610 --> 00:12:52.780
We're building a larger
ecosystem of devices,

00:12:52.780 --> 00:12:55.250
from televisions
to set-top boxes

00:12:55.250 --> 00:12:57.370
and streaming devices for audio.

00:12:57.370 --> 00:12:59.740
This year, we rolled out
audio devices powered

00:12:59.740 --> 00:13:01.580
by Google Cast for audio.

00:13:01.580 --> 00:13:05.420
And Chromecast continues
to see tremendous success.

00:13:05.420 --> 00:13:08.030
Here at I/O 2015,
we'll show you how

00:13:08.030 --> 00:13:09.546
we're improving
the Cast experience

00:13:09.546 --> 00:13:11.420
by unlocking even more
opportunities for game

00:13:11.420 --> 00:13:13.250
developers.

00:13:13.250 --> 00:13:15.840
And what does that mean for
you as a game developer?

00:13:15.840 --> 00:13:18.130
Across Google Cast,
when games and apps

00:13:18.130 --> 00:13:21.760
are connected to the TV, we see
increased engagement, stronger

00:13:21.760 --> 00:13:24.050
monetization, and
because the living room

00:13:24.050 --> 00:13:27.210
is inherently social, you have
multiplayer games that result

00:13:27.210 --> 00:13:29.140
in more downloads for you.

00:13:29.140 --> 00:13:31.800
Because you can utilize the
power of a mobile device,

00:13:31.800 --> 00:13:33.740
all the power of that
platform, like payments,

00:13:33.740 --> 00:13:37.130
already exist and
are available to you.

00:13:37.130 --> 00:13:40.240
Just a few months
ago, in November 2014,

00:13:40.240 --> 00:13:43.390
we released our first wave
of games for Google Cast.

00:13:43.390 --> 00:13:45.480
These games are really
fun, and we worked closely

00:13:45.480 --> 00:13:47.460
with some great partners
to make those games happen.

00:13:47.460 --> 00:13:49.043
Some of those partners
are here today,

00:13:49.043 --> 00:13:50.459
which I'm very happy about.

00:13:50.459 --> 00:13:53.000
I want to take a little bit of
time to talk about these games

00:13:53.000 --> 00:13:55.155
because they're really
great examples of how

00:13:55.155 --> 00:13:57.530
to design a Cast game, in case
you didn't get to try them

00:13:57.530 --> 00:13:59.674
yourself.

00:13:59.674 --> 00:14:02.520
If you played any of these
games, especially Just Dance

00:14:02.520 --> 00:14:04.460
Now by Ubisoft,
I've expect you've

00:14:04.460 --> 00:14:06.750
got some good moves by now.

00:14:06.750 --> 00:14:09.790
As for the Cast team,
well-- as a group

00:14:09.790 --> 00:14:12.179
we're better at dancing than
we were a few months ago.

00:14:12.179 --> 00:14:14.470
But this is a game that really
uses your mobile devices

00:14:14.470 --> 00:14:16.510
sensors to detect
how you're moving,

00:14:16.510 --> 00:14:19.010
or whether you're just standing
there and pumping your fist,

00:14:19.010 --> 00:14:20.593
or you're like really
getting involved

00:14:20.593 --> 00:14:23.280
in using your whole body.

00:14:23.280 --> 00:14:25.480
Classic family fun
is also a great theme

00:14:25.480 --> 00:14:26.844
for Google Cast games.

00:14:26.844 --> 00:14:28.510
That's why we worked
closely with Hasbro

00:14:28.510 --> 00:14:30.960
to bring adaptations of some
of your favorite board games

00:14:30.960 --> 00:14:33.324
to the big screen.

00:14:33.324 --> 00:14:35.365
If dancing isn't your
thing, maybe SCRABBLE Blitz

00:14:35.365 --> 00:14:37.170
is more your speed.

00:14:37.170 --> 00:14:38.730
It's fast.

00:14:38.730 --> 00:14:39.487
It's intense.

00:14:39.487 --> 00:14:41.570
And guess what, you actually
have to spell things.

00:14:41.570 --> 00:14:44.070
There's no AutoCorrect
here to help you out.

00:14:44.070 --> 00:14:45.510
We also have other
classic brands

00:14:45.510 --> 00:14:49.152
like CONNECT 4 Quads, Monopoly
Dash, and SIMON Swipe.

00:14:49.152 --> 00:14:51.110
You should check out some
of these great games.

00:14:51.110 --> 00:14:53.982
They really are
fun for all ages.

00:14:53.982 --> 00:14:55.690
And game shows are
really fun too, right?

00:14:55.690 --> 00:14:57.090
You guys like game shows.

00:14:57.090 --> 00:14:59.640
If you think about it,
almost every great game show

00:14:59.640 --> 00:15:01.750
has some sort of big
board full of fun

00:15:01.750 --> 00:15:03.497
and prizes and surprises.

00:15:03.497 --> 00:15:05.330
When we worked with
Sony Pictures Television

00:15:05.330 --> 00:15:07.030
on Wheel of Fortune,
we saw how much fun

00:15:07.030 --> 00:15:09.120
that could be to use
your TV as the big board

00:15:09.120 --> 00:15:12.000
while controlling the game
with your mobile device.

00:15:12.000 --> 00:15:14.410
By using a game show
format for your design,

00:15:14.410 --> 00:15:15.670
you too can play at home.

00:15:15.670 --> 00:15:17.425
You might not win a
giant bundle of cash

00:15:17.425 --> 00:15:19.340
or win a lifetime
supply of shaving cream,

00:15:19.340 --> 00:15:21.950
but you will have a lot of fun.

00:15:21.950 --> 00:15:24.102
We also had developers
making games on their own

00:15:24.102 --> 00:15:25.560
and publishing them
to Google Play.

00:15:25.560 --> 00:15:27.550
It's really that
easy to make a game.

00:15:27.550 --> 00:15:30.987
We noticed a game called Emoji
Party for Chromecast by Troido

00:15:30.987 --> 00:15:33.320
And we reached out to them
and worked with them directly

00:15:33.320 --> 00:15:35.380
to fully utilize
the Cast experience.

00:15:35.380 --> 00:15:38.370
It's a fun game where these
movie titles pop up on the TV.

00:15:38.370 --> 00:15:40.479
And they're all
encoded in Emoji speak.

00:15:40.479 --> 00:15:42.770
You compete with your friends
to see who can guess them

00:15:42.770 --> 00:15:44.061
first and earn the most points.

00:15:44.061 --> 00:15:46.240
And in this game in
particular, ten players

00:15:46.240 --> 00:15:48.765
are connected at the same
time through one television.

00:15:48.765 --> 00:15:51.610
Can anybody guess
what this one is?

00:15:51.610 --> 00:15:52.110
Yeah, okay.

00:15:52.110 --> 00:15:54.130
This is a easy one.

00:15:54.130 --> 00:15:56.220
Planet of the Apes.

00:15:56.220 --> 00:15:58.306
These types of
games go a long way

00:15:58.306 --> 00:16:00.180
toward fulfilling a
dream for game developers

00:16:00.180 --> 00:16:02.230
to enable people to
play games on their TVs

00:16:02.230 --> 00:16:04.350
without expensive game consoles.

00:16:04.350 --> 00:16:06.739
These games are great for
Cast-- all these ones I just

00:16:06.739 --> 00:16:07.280
talked about.

00:16:07.280 --> 00:16:10.320
They're social, they utilize
the phones and tablets

00:16:10.320 --> 00:16:12.770
people already love
using, and they're

00:16:12.770 --> 00:16:16.620
surprising in the fun way
that they achieve game play

00:16:16.620 --> 00:16:18.379
with simple, accessible design.

00:16:18.379 --> 00:16:20.920
If you're interested in learning
more about the core concepts

00:16:20.920 --> 00:16:23.820
and principles of designing
great games for Google Cast,

00:16:23.820 --> 00:16:25.830
check out the talk
that I'm giving called

00:16:25.830 --> 00:16:28.210
Designing Games for Google
Cast here at I/O tomorrow

00:16:28.210 --> 00:16:31.134
at 9:00 AM in alcove two.

00:16:31.134 --> 00:16:32.550
And all the games
I just discussed

00:16:32.550 --> 00:16:36.820
were made using the Google
Cast SDK we released last year.

00:16:36.820 --> 00:16:39.460
They use a model we call
a Receiver Cast Game.

00:16:39.460 --> 00:16:42.040
An app running on the sender,
which is your mobile device,

00:16:42.040 --> 00:16:43.730
connects to a
receiver device, which

00:16:43.730 --> 00:16:46.560
is any device like a
Chromecast, and passes along

00:16:46.560 --> 00:16:49.160
the information the
receiver needs to load

00:16:49.160 --> 00:16:51.300
the game from the cloud.

00:16:51.300 --> 00:16:52.980
In a typical
Chromecast application,

00:16:52.980 --> 00:16:56.355
like a video on demand app, this
is a really simple transaction.

00:16:56.355 --> 00:16:57.730
But when you make
a game, there's

00:16:57.730 --> 00:16:59.370
a lot of interaction
that's going on.

00:16:59.370 --> 00:17:02.180
And it's going to happen
between multiple devices or web

00:17:02.180 --> 00:17:03.282
browsers.

00:17:03.282 --> 00:17:05.740
During our partnership with
the titles I mentioned earlier,

00:17:05.740 --> 00:17:07.339
we found one big
way that we could

00:17:07.339 --> 00:17:10.200
and help to improve
the game development

00:17:10.200 --> 00:17:12.215
experience for developers.

00:17:12.215 --> 00:17:14.589
That's why here at I/O, we're
announcing the game manager

00:17:14.589 --> 00:17:16.660
APIs for Google Cast.

00:17:16.660 --> 00:17:18.990
The game manager APIs
make it faster and easier

00:17:18.990 --> 00:17:20.810
for game developers,
like yourself,

00:17:20.810 --> 00:17:23.619
to Cast-enable their apps across
all the devices we support,

00:17:23.619 --> 00:17:26.020
which is Android, iOS,
and Chrome browsers,

00:17:26.020 --> 00:17:29.660
and get those devices connected
to a Chromecast or Android TV.

00:17:29.660 --> 00:17:31.620
All the synchronization
between players

00:17:31.620 --> 00:17:33.530
is handled through
the Cast receiver,

00:17:33.530 --> 00:17:34.650
which is the Chromecast.

00:17:34.650 --> 00:17:36.730
It acts like a
server for the match,

00:17:36.730 --> 00:17:38.230
and will store all
the game state,

00:17:38.230 --> 00:17:40.660
and take the role of pushing
notifications to the devices

00:17:40.660 --> 00:17:42.997
when new information
is available.

00:17:42.997 --> 00:17:45.080
We're excited to see what
kind of innovative games

00:17:45.080 --> 00:17:47.750
you'll create and build
using the game manager

00:17:47.750 --> 00:17:49.110
APIs for Google Cast.

00:17:49.110 --> 00:17:52.290
And now it's even faster and
easier than it was before.

00:17:52.290 --> 00:17:53.665
If you want to
hear more details,

00:17:53.665 --> 00:17:55.998
check out the box talks we
have going on tomorrow called

00:17:55.998 --> 00:17:58.535
Game Manager APIs for Google
Cast, where our engineers will

00:17:58.535 --> 00:18:00.840
walk you through the
implementation of Google Cast

00:18:00.840 --> 00:18:03.789
Managers APIs.

00:18:03.789 --> 00:18:05.580
Also be sure to check
out our sandbox booth

00:18:05.580 --> 00:18:08.010
on the third floor to check
out demos of the games I just

00:18:08.010 --> 00:18:11.940
mentioned and some other ones
that we have in development,

00:18:11.940 --> 00:18:16.590
Catch Phrase by Hasbro and
Tricky Titans by MediaMonks.

00:18:16.590 --> 00:18:18.360
In Catch Phrase,
the classic game

00:18:18.360 --> 00:18:21.210
comes to Cast as two player
stand in front of the screen

00:18:21.210 --> 00:18:23.871
and everyone in the room can
see the catch phrase on the TV.

00:18:23.871 --> 00:18:26.120
I don't know if you saw us
playing this earlier today.

00:18:26.120 --> 00:18:28.505
Everyone goes crazy shouting
clues at the guessers

00:18:28.505 --> 00:18:29.880
and points are
scored by pressing

00:18:29.880 --> 00:18:31.449
a button on the mobile device.

00:18:31.449 --> 00:18:33.240
You can expect this
one to be fun and loud.

00:18:33.240 --> 00:18:37.350
So please come play
it with us upstairs.

00:18:37.350 --> 00:18:38.900
MediaMonks created
a fun game called

00:18:38.900 --> 00:18:41.600
Tricky Titan with great visuals
and strategic turn based

00:18:41.600 --> 00:18:42.480
game play.

00:18:42.480 --> 00:18:45.300
These giant titans are
sitting on top of villages

00:18:45.300 --> 00:18:49.240
and they use large shovels
to scoop up houses and people

00:18:49.240 --> 00:18:50.810
and throw them at each other.

00:18:50.810 --> 00:18:51.831
It's really clever.

00:18:51.831 --> 00:18:54.330
Both games are in development
and are using the Game Manager

00:18:54.330 --> 00:18:56.506
APIs already.

00:18:56.506 --> 00:18:57.880
Now you might be
asking yourself,

00:18:57.880 --> 00:19:00.070
we have this giant
TV, a Chromecast,

00:19:00.070 --> 00:19:01.940
and an amazing
computer in our pocket.

00:19:01.940 --> 00:19:03.600
Couldn't we do a
little bit more?

00:19:03.600 --> 00:19:05.000
Well, of course we can.

00:19:05.000 --> 00:19:09.339
That's why we created the Remote
Display APIs for Google Cast.

00:19:09.339 --> 00:19:11.630
There are millions of mobile
devices with powerful GPUs

00:19:11.630 --> 00:19:15.130
and sensors ready to send
amazing interactive content

00:19:15.130 --> 00:19:17.250
to the largest
screen in the home.

00:19:17.250 --> 00:19:19.140
With the Remote Display
APIs for Google Cast,

00:19:19.140 --> 00:19:21.650
this is now possible.

00:19:21.650 --> 00:19:23.390
Remote Display for
Android and iOS

00:19:23.390 --> 00:19:25.700
allows app developers
to take full advantage

00:19:25.700 --> 00:19:27.814
of the multiscreen
Google Cast model.

00:19:27.814 --> 00:19:29.480
This is really important
and it supports

00:19:29.480 --> 00:19:32.050
one of our key principles
of cross platform

00:19:32.050 --> 00:19:34.050
compatibility for Google Cast.

00:19:34.050 --> 00:19:37.784
Whether you and your friends
own an Android device or an iOS

00:19:37.784 --> 00:19:39.450
device and they come
over to your house,

00:19:39.450 --> 00:19:42.560
you can all play
together and have fun.

00:19:42.560 --> 00:19:44.030
So integrating
Remote Display means

00:19:44.030 --> 00:19:46.810
you can harness all of those
increasingly powerful CPUs

00:19:46.810 --> 00:19:49.940
and GPUs in your phone and
build dual display games

00:19:49.940 --> 00:19:52.170
were you use the phone to
render both a local display

00:19:52.170 --> 00:19:53.490
and a virtual one.

00:19:53.490 --> 00:19:55.790
And we handle sending the
virtual display directly

00:19:55.790 --> 00:19:58.300
to the large screen
via our Cast protocol.

00:19:58.300 --> 00:20:01.770
As a developer, that means
bigger games, more screens,

00:20:01.770 --> 00:20:03.900
and more fun.

00:20:03.900 --> 00:20:06.210
With a remote display,
you trigger the experience

00:20:06.210 --> 00:20:08.354
directly from within
your game or app.

00:20:08.354 --> 00:20:09.770
It follows the
same simple model I

00:20:09.770 --> 00:20:12.220
discussed earlier of all our
Google Cast interactions.

00:20:12.220 --> 00:20:14.480
Just tap the Cast button and go.

00:20:14.480 --> 00:20:16.854
It increases the
discoverability of the feature

00:20:16.854 --> 00:20:18.270
and it's a big
difference compared

00:20:18.270 --> 00:20:19.790
to competing technologies.

00:20:19.790 --> 00:20:22.370
You don't have to rely on the
player to exit the app or game

00:20:22.370 --> 00:20:24.310
and turn on some
system level feature.

00:20:24.310 --> 00:20:27.680
They can have the experience
you intended them to have.

00:20:27.680 --> 00:20:30.410
For example, in Ubisoft's
racing game, Driver Speedboat

00:20:30.410 --> 00:20:32.760
Paradise, you can blast
through dangerous waves

00:20:32.760 --> 00:20:34.520
and jump off ramps to
fly through the air

00:20:34.520 --> 00:20:36.380
and perform impressive stunts.

00:20:36.380 --> 00:20:39.730
The team uses cutting edge 3D
graphics, Triple A effects,

00:20:39.730 --> 00:20:42.750
and HD textures on a mobile
device sent across the room

00:20:42.750 --> 00:20:44.770
to your screen.

00:20:44.770 --> 00:20:46.470
And speedboat racing
is a lot of fun,

00:20:46.470 --> 00:20:48.460
but maybe you'd like
a nice game of tennis.

00:20:48.460 --> 00:20:50.900
Rolocule has this
fun casual tennis

00:20:50.900 --> 00:20:52.290
game called Motion Tennis.

00:20:52.290 --> 00:20:53.630
You hold the phone in
your hand like a tennis

00:20:53.630 --> 00:20:55.838
racquet and swing your arm
to choose the type of shot

00:20:55.838 --> 00:20:57.610
to make next.

00:20:57.610 --> 00:21:00.490
It's fun, intuitive, and
great for multiple players,

00:21:00.490 --> 00:21:02.610
but you need to hold
on to your phone tight.

00:21:02.610 --> 00:21:04.530
If you're an inventor,
you might want

00:21:04.530 --> 00:21:07.624
to consider making some
really cool phone strap

00:21:07.624 --> 00:21:09.790
technology or something
because in the coming years,

00:21:09.790 --> 00:21:11.590
I think the screen
repair guys are going

00:21:11.590 --> 00:21:14.360
to love this remote display
technology as things

00:21:14.360 --> 00:21:16.430
fly across the room.

00:21:16.430 --> 00:21:17.930
And we've all heard
the phrase, when

00:21:17.930 --> 00:21:20.650
pigs fly, and for many
of us, myself included,

00:21:20.650 --> 00:21:23.080
that's especially true
about going to the gym.

00:21:23.080 --> 00:21:24.090
Now with Fitflap!

00:21:24.090 --> 00:21:25.522
by BreakFirst,
you can play games

00:21:25.522 --> 00:21:26.730
and get fit at the same time.

00:21:26.730 --> 00:21:27.850
And this really works.

00:21:27.850 --> 00:21:30.124
I was in some pain
from testing this game.

00:21:30.124 --> 00:21:31.540
The game is really
cool because it

00:21:31.540 --> 00:21:33.760
uses image recognition
and the front

00:21:33.760 --> 00:21:36.160
facing camera on the
phone to control the pig.

00:21:36.160 --> 00:21:38.930
You really flap your
arms and make the pig fly

00:21:38.930 --> 00:21:41.240
and collect coins while
dodging obstacles.

00:21:41.240 --> 00:21:44.040
And I could tell you everybody
at the office had fun laughing

00:21:44.040 --> 00:21:46.270
at me when I demoed this
to them for the first time.

00:21:46.270 --> 00:21:49.640
And you really have to get your
pig, which is me, in shape.

00:21:49.640 --> 00:21:52.000
So in between flights, you
can go dance with your pig

00:21:52.000 --> 00:21:55.870
or run in place while your
pig runs on the treadmill.

00:21:55.870 --> 00:21:58.450
And just like these games,
your real creative genius

00:21:58.450 --> 00:22:01.310
shows itself when you combine
great social multiplayer

00:22:01.310 --> 00:22:03.722
with the power of mobile
devices and the big screen.

