00:27:07.760 --> 00:27:10.230
So let's start with
Player Analytics.

00:27:10.230 --> 00:27:12.890
It's a set of reports
in the developer console

00:27:12.890 --> 00:27:15.795
that we launched at GDC
earlier in the year.

00:27:15.795 --> 00:27:17.920
And throughout the development
of Player Analytics,

00:27:17.920 --> 00:27:20.710
we worked very
closely with Eric,

00:27:20.710 --> 00:27:24.350
the developer of BombSquad,
who I mentioned earlier.

00:27:24.350 --> 00:27:26.890
And as we integrated over
different prototypes,

00:27:26.890 --> 00:27:29.800
we discovered we needed
a deeper understanding

00:27:29.800 --> 00:27:31.640
of BombSquad's in-game economy.

00:27:31.640 --> 00:27:35.300
So we developed something called
the Sources and Sinks Report.

00:27:35.300 --> 00:27:37.590
The Sources and
Sinks Report helps

00:27:37.590 --> 00:27:40.170
developers understand
the relationship

00:27:40.170 --> 00:27:43.300
between the rate at which
players earn a premium

00:27:43.300 --> 00:27:47.300
currency, like gold coins,
or emeralds, or tickets

00:27:47.300 --> 00:27:51.760
in Eric's case, and the rate
at which players consume that.

00:27:51.760 --> 00:27:54.020
In an ideal world,
the rate at which

00:27:54.020 --> 00:27:58.050
a player earns currency and
consumes currency roughly

00:27:58.050 --> 00:27:58.875
nets out to zero.

00:28:01.670 --> 00:28:04.520
