when a game is available.

00:34:12.800 --> 00:34:15.699
It's a powerful user
acquisition tool

00:34:15.699 --> 00:34:20.710
that allows developers to
create large day one releases.

00:34:20.710 --> 00:34:23.489
And in markets like
Japan and Korea

00:34:23.489 --> 00:34:25.830
that pioneered this
practice, we've

00:34:25.830 --> 00:34:29.420
scene pre-registration result
in millions of day one users

00:34:29.420 --> 00:34:31.770
of the game, instantly
bootstrapping

00:34:31.770 --> 00:34:34.370
the game's ecosystem,
it's community,

00:34:34.370 --> 00:34:37.510
and providing a huge boost
to store rankings right out

00:34:37.510 --> 00:34:38.600
of the gate.

